-- Real Madrid Plans $40.3 Million Bid for Steven Gerrard, The People Reports
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2011-02-06T12:48:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-06/real-madrid-plans-40-3-million-bid-for-steven-gerrard-the-people-reports.html
Real Madrid coach  Jose Mourinho  is
planning a 25 million-pound ($40.3 million) bid for Liverpool
captain  Steven Gerrard , the People reported, without saying
where it got the information.  Mourinho is set to stay at the Spanish soccer club for
another season after winning a dispute with sporting director
Jorge Valdano and has persuaded President Florentino Perez to
bid for Gerrard, the newspaper said.   Atletico Madrid striker Sergio Aguero is also a target for
Mourinho, the People added.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  